Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain, then rinse potatoes under cold water; transfer to a #large bowl{} and refrigerate until ready to use.

While potatoes cook, toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> Lower heat to medium if chicken is browning too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken for pork. Pork is also suggested in original recipe.

To bowl with cooled potatoes, add scallion whites, @smoky mustard{1%ounce}, and @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}; stir until thoroughly combined. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

Return pan used for chicken to stovetop over medium heat. Add @honey{4%teaspoon}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Return chicken to pan and cook, turning occasionally, until fully coated and glazed, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

> Glaze chicken as instructed.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, potato salad, and broccoli between plates. Spoon any remaining glaze over chicken. Sprinkle scallion greens over potato salad and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.